reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars High-Performance Connectivity with Highwings 8K 10K HDMI Cable
reviews.reviewText: I recently upgraded my home entertainment setup with the Highwings 8K 10K HDMI Cable, and the results have been nothing short of impressive. This certified Ultra High Speed HDMI® cable delivers on its promise of high-performance connectivity.High Data Transfer Rate (5/5):The standout feature of the Highwings HDMI cable is its incredible 48Gbps data transfer rate. This ensures seamless transmission of high-resolution content, making it ideal for 8K and 10K displays. The cable supports the latest HDMI specifications, providing a future-proof solution for evolving multimedia needs.8K and 10K Resolution (5/5):Whether you're a cinephile, gamer, or content creator, the Highwings HDMI cable unlocks the full potential of your 8K and 10K devices. The cable's capability to transmit crystal-clear visuals and vibrant colors enhances the viewing and gaming experience, bringing content to life with stunning detail.Certified Ultra High Speed (5/5):The certification as an Ultra High Speed HDMI® cable instills confidence in its performance and reliability. It meets the stringent standards set for high-speed data transmission, ensuring that it can handle the demands of the latest audio-visual technologies without compromise.Durable Braided Design (5/5):The braided design of the cable not only adds a touch of elegance but also enhances durability. The braiding provides additional protection against wear, bending, and potential damage, making the Highwings HDMI cable a robust and long-lasting investment.Length and Flexibility (5/5):The 6.6FT/2M length strikes a perfect balance between flexibility and practicality. It provides ample reach for connecting devices while minimizing excess cable clutter. The flexibility of the cable makes it easy to route and manage behind entertainment centers or within wall-mounted setups.Wide Compatibility (5/5):The Highwings HDMI cable is compatible with a wide range of devices, including 8K and 10K TVs, gaming consoles, Blu-ray players, and more. Its versatility ensures that it can seamlessly integrate into various home theater and gaming setups without compatibility concerns.Gold-Plated Connectors (4.5/5):The gold-plated connectors contribute to stable signal transmission and resistance to corrosion. While gold-plating is a common and effective choice for connectors, additional reinforcement in critical areas could further enhance the cable's durability over time.Value for Money (5/5):Considering the high data transfer rate, certification, durable design, and wide compatibility, the Highwings 8K 10K HDMI Cable offers excellent value for money. It's a worthy investment for anyone seeking top-tier performance in their multimedia setups.Conclusion:In conclusion, the Highwings 8K 10K HDMI Cable stands out as a reliable and high-performance solution for demanding audio-visual applications. Its data transfer capabilities, build quality, and compatibility make it a top choice for those who prioritize quality connectivity in their home entertainment systems.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Works fine but something is weird
reviews.reviewText: In first place, i give only 4 stars just as a precaution, please, read the last paragraph.Effectively this is a certified "Ultra High Speed HDMI Cable", i've verified with the "HDMI Cable" app, that's a good start.In my case i've used to connect my RTX3080 12GB to a Samsung 50" Neo QLED 4K QN90A (QN50QN90AAK),with previows cables from other weird brands i was suffering of random flickering, sometimes just a couple in 1 hour; with this cable as far as i've tested the flicker is gone, even using the most demanding resolution that my rig can achieve, 3840x2160 @120Hz 10bit YCbCr444; no artifacts, no sound issues, variable refresh rate works fine too, overall it works as expected, i'm satisfied in this regard wtihout doubts.HOWEVER, i must be clear, there is something weird here that is good that you know, at least in my case, if i use the Samsung built in function to test the hdmi cable the test fails and it recommends to replace the cable, to be honest i don't know if that test is reliable, at least in my real life test this is the 1st cable that works properly without any issues, maybe at 144Hz there can be issues, i have no way to test at that refresh rate so i don't know.
